== Introduction ==
'''Sudoku''' is a UI application and it plays like normal sudoku puzzle games. It is a logic-based number-placement puzzle. The objective is to fill a 9×9 grid so that each column, each row, and each of the nine 3×3 boxes (also called blocks or regions) contains the digits from 1 to 9 only one time each. The puzzle setter provides a partially completed grid. For more information, refer to the [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sudoku  Sudoku rules].

